<p>How I can do to make me these two queries return the same results?</p>  <p><code>móvil</code> vs. <code>movil</code></p>  <p><strong>Table rows:</strong> <br>INSERT [Palabras] ([Id], [texto]) VALUES (1, N'Movil iphone 6')<br> INSERT [Palabras] ([Id], [texto]) VALUES (2, N'Móvil iphone 6')<br> INSERT [Palabras] ([Id], [texto]) VALUES (3, N'Moviles iphone 6')<br> INSERT [Palabras] ([Id], [texto]) VALUES (4, N'Móviles iphone 6')<br></p>  <p>Returns 4 rows:</p>  <pre><code>SELECT * FROM Palabras WHERE CONTAINS(*, N'FORMSOF(INFLECTIONAL, "móvil", 3082, NULL, 0)'); </code></pre>  <p>Returns 2 rows:<br> Only returns: <em>Movil iphone 6</em> , <em>Móvil iphone 6</em></p>  <pre><code>SELECT * FROM Palabras WHERE CONTAINS(*, N'FORMSOF(INFLECTIONAL, "movil", 3082, NULL, 0)') </code></pre>  <p><br><br> <strong>View the tokenization result of a word breaker, thesaurus, and stoplist combination:</strong></p>  <pre><code>SELECT * FROM sys.dm_fts_parser(N'FORMSOF(INFLECTIONAL, "móvil")', 3082, NULL, 0); </code></pre>  <p>Display_term: <code>moviles</code>, <code>movil</code></p>  <pre><code>SELECT * FROM sys.dm_fts_parser(N'FORMSOF(INFLECTIONAL, "movil")', 3082, NULL, 0); </code></pre>  <p>Display_term: <code>movil</code></p>